2026-04-20 | failure-agent | version 0.7.0
Summary:
- Added indexed failure references and remote index builders so `failure-agent` can query CANN errors, ACLNN APIs, and MindSpore mint API mappings from skill-local structured indexes.

Detailed changes:
- Added default runtime DB indexes under `reference/index/` for CANN error codes, CANN ACLNN APIs, and MindSpore mint API facts.
- Added `scripts/query_cann_index.py` and `scripts/query_mint_api_index.py` as read-only CLI entrypoints for diagnosis-time index lookup.
- Added `scripts/index_builders/generate_cann_failure_index.py` and `scripts/index_builders/generate_mindspore_failure_index.py` as skill-local one-shot builders for rebuilding the indexed references.
- Added `scripts/index_builders/mint_api_methodology.md` to document the MindSpore mint index builder rules and field semantics.
- Updated `SKILL.md` and runtime references to route CANN, ACLNN, MindSpore, PTA, and mint-scoped failures through the new DB/query-script flow while preserving manual-only and Factory-read-only boundaries.
- Expanded `failure-showcase.md`, `mindspore-diagnosis.md`, `pta-diagnosis.md`, `mindspore-api-reference.md`, and `cann-api-reference.md` with index-backed routing guidance.
- Added `.gitignore` handling for builder temporary workspaces and updated `skill.yaml` metadata.
- Consolidated index-related tests into `tests/test_indexes.py`, keeping mint DB semantic regression coverage while removing default-release dependence on optional YAML exports and local absolute MindSpore checkout paths.
- Simplified structure tests to validate the default runtime surface: core references, query scripts, helper scripts, and default DB indexes.
- Added human-readable pretty JSON output for query scripts via `--pretty` / `-p` while preserving compact JSON as the default automation format.
- Exposed mint ACLNN facts directly in `query_mint_api_index.py` `api` and `explain` outputs so DB query results include the same `aclnn` structure as the YAML export.
- Clarified `query_mint_api_index.py --module` as mint-relative and added compatibility for bare `--name` queries.

